The '''white Wolves''' were a type of wolf native to the frozen lands in the north of [[Middle-earth]]. They were not normally seen in [[Eriador]], but seem to have remained among the snows of the [[Northern Waste|Forodwaith]] and perhaps beyond.{{Fact}}

In the year {{TA|2911}}, one of the harshest winters in Middle-earth's history descended, the so-called [[Fell Winter (Third Age)|Fell Winter]].<ref>{{App|TA}}</ref> The ice and snow of the north came at least as far south as [[the Shire]]. With them came the white Wolves, invading Eriador and roaming as far south as the Shire. The frozen [[Brandywine]] River meant that they were even able to cross into the [[Eastfarthing]]. This was the last time the [[Horn-call of Buckland]] was used before the [[War of the Ring]], one hundred and seven years later.<ref>{{FR|I11}}, pp. 231, 375</ref>

